Implemented the Node.js/Express file-sharing app in the workspace.

Created:
- `package.json`
- `README.md`
- `.env.example`
- `src/app.js`
- `src/db.js`
- EJS views under `src/views/`
- CSS under `src/public/styles.css`

Key security features included: bcrypt password hashing, parameterized SQLite queries, CSRF protection, Helmet security headers, rate limiting, escaped EJS output, ownership checks on downloads/deletes, generic error responses, random server-side upload filenames, content-inspected file allow-listing, upload size limits, and path containment for file access.

I did not run/install/build/test the app. The README explains local setup on port `5045`; for production HTTPS, set `COOKIE_SECURE=true`.
